text: Tapuae Marine Reserve is a marine reserve created in 2008 off the Taranaki coast of New Zealand. It protects an area of 1404 ha and adjoins the Sugar Loaf Islands Marine Protected Area. ==References== ==External links== *Tapuae Marine Reserve at the Department of Conservation Category:Marine reserves of New Zealand Category:New Plymouth District Category:Protected areas established in 2008 Category:Protected areas of Taranaki Category:2008 establishments in New Zealand
